body:
When the verilator is used on the following file:

```systemverilog
module dut(output int x);
   parameter int P [5];
   assign x = P[2];
endmodule
​
module top(output int o);
   dut #(.P('{1, 2, 3, 4, 5})) u_dut(.x(o));
endmodule
```
The error `%Error: Internal Error: ../V3Width.cpp:134: Width dtype request on self-determined or preliminary VUP` is thrown.

It works well in case when the pattern is the default value of that parameter, like here:
```systemverilog
module dut(output int x);
   parameter int P [5] = '{1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
   assign x = P[2];
endmodule

module top(output int o);
   dut u_dut(.x(o));
endmodule
```
